  <sec sec-type="overview">
    <title>Overview of the Package <monospace>lcc</monospace> and r syntax</title>
    <p>This section provides some details on the implementation of the function lcc and explains its technical arguments, whose default settings were carefully chosen. The package is freely available for download from the CRAN website <uri xlink:href="https://CRAN.R-project.org/package=lcc">https://CRAN.R-project.org/package=lcc</uri>, and installation can be performed using</p>
    <p><monospace>R&gt; install.packages(</monospace>“<monospace>lcc</monospace>”<monospace>)</monospace></p>
    <p>
      <monospace>R&gt; library(lcc)</monospace>
    </p>
    <p>The <monospace>lcc</monospace> package has 21 arguments that are briefly summarised in <xref rid="table-1" ref-type="table">Table 1</xref>.</p>
