    <p>5. <monospace>pdmat</monospace>: the <monospace>lcc</monospace> package provides six standard classes of positive-definite matrix structures that can be included in the model to estimate the LCC, LPC and LA statistics. Available standard classes are <monospace>pdSymm</monospace>, <monospace>pdLogChol</monospace>, <monospace>pdDiag</monospace>, <monospace>pdIdent</monospace>, <monospace>pdCompSymm</monospace> and <monospace>pdNatural</monospace>. More information about these classes are available in <xref rid="ref-29" ref-type="bibr">Pinheiro &amp; Bates (2000)</xref>.</p>
    <p>6. <monospace>var.class</monospace>: a class of variance functions that are used to model the variance structure of within-group errors using covariates (<xref rid="ref-29" ref-type="bibr">Pinheiro &amp; Bates, 2000</xref>). We generalize this class as
